{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":139046,"duration_api_ms":138493,"num_turns":17,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"ec0540d2-9a4a-4593-9aba-c12a7948af45","total_cost_usd":0.7295945,"usage":{"input_tokens":14,"cache_creation_input_tokens":54826,"cache_read_input_tokens":604074,"output_tokens":3393,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":54826,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":14,"outputTokens":3393,"cacheReadInputTokens":604074,"cacheCreationInputTokens":54826,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.7295945,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"amendments":[{"body":"The service-level `update_task_run` function only rewrites the NDJSON lineage file but does NOT update the MilestoneSnapshot (progress counters: in_progress_beads, completed_beads, failed_beads; active_bead). By contrast, `record_bead_completion` correctly updates both. If a controller calls `update_task_run` to transition a Running entry to Succeeded/Failed, the snapshot's progress counters and active_bead will become permanently stale. `update_task_run` must also accept `snapshot_store` and `journal_store` parameters and apply the same snapshot mutations and journal event emission that `record_bead_completion` does.","rationale":"This is a data consistency bug. The snapshot is the source of truth for dashboards, status queries, and the `validate_semantics` check. Leaving it unsynchronized after an update defeats the purpose of the new API and will cause incorrect progress reporting."},{"body":"In `record_bead_completion` (service.rs lines 372-376), any non-Succeeded outcome—including `TaskRunOutcome::Skipped`—emits a `MilestoneEventType::BeadFailed` journal event. Skipped should either emit a distinct event type or at minimum not be recorded as a failure. Currently the progress counter also doesn't increment for Skipped (it falls through the match arms), so the total bead accounting is also off when Skipped is used.","rationale":"Skipped and Failed are semantically different. Recording a skip as a failure will pollute audit trails and any alerting or dashboards built on journal events."},{"body":"The relationship between `record_bead_completion` (append-based) and `update_task_run` (in-place-rewrite) is undefined and untested in combination. `record_bead_completion` appends a NEW completion entry alongside the existing Running entry, while `update_task_run` mutates the existing Running entry in place. If both are used for the same bead, the NDJSON file will have an inconsistent mix of append-style and update-style entries. The code should document which one the controller should use and when, and add a test covering what happens if both are called on the same run.","rationale":"Without clear guidance, controller code will use both APIs inconsistently, producing NDJSON files that are hard to interpret and where `find_runs_for_bead` returns confusing results (e.g., a Running entry that was silently mutated to Succeeded plus a separate Succeeded entry for the same logical run)."},{"body":"In the FS adapter, `update_task_run` performs a non-atomic read-modify-write: it reads the entire NDJSON file, deserializes all entries, mutates one, and rewrites the whole file. Between the read and the write, a concurrent `append_task_run` call (e.g., from another process recording a different bead) could add lines that will be silently dropped by the rewrite. At minimum, add a comment documenting this limitation; ideally, use file locking (e.g., `flock`) around the read-modify-write cycle.","rationale":"The existing `append_task_run` is safe for concurrent use (append-only), but `update_task_run` breaks that property. In a multi-process environment (which Ralph appears to be, given tmux session management), silent data loss is possible."}],"summary":"The implementation correctly adds the required fields (run_id, plan_hash, outcome_detail, milestone_id) to TaskRunEntry with proper backward-compatible serde attributes. The FS adapter, find_runs_for_bead query, and backward-compat deserialization are all implemented and tested. However, four significant issues were found: (1) update_task_run doesn't synchronize the MilestoneSnapshot, leaving progress counters stale — this is a data consistency bug; (2) record_bead_completion misclassifies Skipped outcomes as BeadFailed in the journal; (3) the append-vs-update duality between record_bead_completion and update_task_run is undefined and could produce inconsistent NDJSON state; (4) update_task_run's read-modify-write on the NDJSON file is not safe against concurrent appends."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"559cafa3-f2a8-4ae5-ba45-c84215351a98"}
